<subSubSection id="E6D0AF4E9D18BFE77441B974D1A82E05" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="397E3C4F68A25CF552146B746BD5476F" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58D6252FF8D066245BB0A4C432E51D83" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
The new species is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EF31D5DF8F12BC815D09052705B2ED0F" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Otarrha) odonta" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odonta" subGenus="Otarrha">C. (Otarrha) odonta</taxonomicName>
Blahnik, 2002 by some shared primitive characters of the subgenus, like hindwing venation pattern with Rs 4-branched and the undivided anterior head setal warts. Both species also have a simple, subtriangular, and completely divided tergum X and an inner process on each inferior appendage. However, the new species has the 
<taxonomicName id="45D2B2B1FCB5132D3CFD1270C9B1FD81" authorityName="RJ Blahnik" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Otarrha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Otarrha" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ECED67E932312D06591BB43AFA2D3D02" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Otarrha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
synapomorphic hindwing venation with Sc+R1 fused, narrower and more uniform lobes of tergum X, and inferior appendage rhomboidal (in lateral view) and more elongated and spatulated (in ventral view). Additionally, the dorsomesal process of the inferior appendage in 
<taxonomicName id="C5B90F695EC45A1C99163A67049904E1" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Otarrha) paraodonta" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraodonta" subGenus="Otarrha">C. (Otarrha) paraodonta</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7A9B4D5995A194379FE2842DE3CAAACA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is thorn-like, more robust, and positioned subapically; while in 
<taxonomicName id="F62721A9299DAE8F8F9CAE6F0AEE746F" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. odonta" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odonta">
<emphasis id="C7248B563900AD6AB690845AC3BF4D6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">C. odonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this process is tooth-like, blunt, and positioned more apically. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="5A96B7824324106DA822F99D865F036C" class="Insecta" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. (Otarrha) paraodonta" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraodonta" subGenus="Otarrha">C. (Otarrha) paraodonta</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="AB71655EA46722E64FC43FF3B33D2D5B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">sp. nov.</emphasis>
can be recognized by its differently shaped tergum IX as viewed dorsally, the more robust ventral process, and simple phallotremal sclerite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F8B9E029DBB362969B3EFACCE21D48A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="description">
<paragraph id="3425B01B12947A73D67DC9C59BB4BE6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6FBA814B5E8E31B61065BEE10BBB5189" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="8A9C57E44F70D46ADCA49BAA2EFAAE7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Adult male</emphasis>
: forewing length 5.2-5.8 mm (n=3; holotype = 5.8 mm). General color (in alcohol) uniformly golden brown, except dark brown dorsum of head. Dorsum of head with anterior, anteromesal, posterior, and posterolateral setal warts; posterolateral setal warts large; anterior setal warts each elongate and undivided; postocular parietal sclerite large, slightly extending below the eye. Maxillary palps relatively short, 2nd segment shorter than 3rd segment, apicomesally with stout setae. Wing venation typical for the subgenus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3ACF02B2C8964FE1C9E226C9CE5851B7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689955" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">5A-B</figureCitation>
), except Rs of hind wing 4-branched (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B7691F1134F7EEA36966C95F3B42FE4A" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689955" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">5B</figureCitation>
); forewing with forks I, II, III, and V present, stem of Rs almost straight, crossveins 
<emphasis id="DF6D8EF7ADDAD0D70DF26DDED7CC70BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">s</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="46DEE6091B321C7A8902427F98357ADD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">r-m</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="889F3EE96BE546C836C471A9F6C140A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m</emphasis>
linearly arranged and unpigmented, crossveins 
<emphasis id="99421E34C39CC6B49A5F1AD44605DF90" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m-cu</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="9BE384E1E2D1F668A565D6BCE91F653B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">cu</emphasis>
and apex of Cu2 also hyaline; 2A not forked (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E79717EF1D32E803868AD9F9BC769AD7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689955" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">5A</figureCitation>
); hind wing with forks I, II and V present, R1 and Sc fused; crossveins 
<emphasis id="81214F99E99D782B84FE594FE4F3D6CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">s</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="49F5F4817640F72DFEFB2B3A4EDEB701" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">r-m</emphasis>
not aligned and unpigmented, crossvein 
<emphasis id="8AACCD81B2AA579F1B68C2A560C46113" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">m-cu</emphasis>
apparently absent, 
<emphasis id="4C7C4519F0D6EFE11FAF86B7CA14A7D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">cu-a</emphasis>
present, anal loop very small (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A5CF9A3957481E8A4103C30E05E3FBA" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype wing venation: A right forewing; B right hind wing. Abbreviations: DC, discoidal cell; MC, medial cell; TC, thyridial cell." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689955" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">5B</figureCitation>
). Tibial spur formula 1-4-4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DFD69FCD4F026B22121FACCBB157FE12" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="E0C05AFDF27B946BF236F980CB14F92E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B251B39B6BABF8628E000CBFBF2441DD" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6</figureCitation>
): Segment IX, dorsally with anterior margin deeply concave, posterior margin almost straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="935A9F6D26635C92577771EB906FD8D9" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6B</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, with anterior margin almost straight, somewhat projected in the anteroventral portion; posterior margin sinuous, with distinct dorsomedial and ventromedial invagination (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3E87A477F52F283A54DF6FB28F097508" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A</figureCitation>
); ventral process elongate, about same length of inferior appendage as viewed laterally, enlarging apically with rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="36F9FB18C14319B88BB4A305A05CA9BC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1CA1B84E3EAFF9C9058980D59560FE41" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6C</figureCitation>
). Tergum X, in dorsal view, completely divided mesally, forming elongate, paired narrow sclerotized lobes, slightly tapering apically; apex rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FB237557772F523A934714D5FBBD9271" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6B</figureCitation>
); each lobe with numerous apical and basoventral sensilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="632C9E1D3D0C9BB3E4530BDFCA09FE24" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="638E8C297EF04CACE08D98CD62853394" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6B</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, subtriangular (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="247CD7FF04A0B1CB75280ACCAB114F35" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A</figureCitation>
). Preanal appendages flattened, earlike, laterally directed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FCB9D72953F57E2E2DC7FC8D64306983" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A, B</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages, in lateral view, rhomboidal, relatively short (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="55AB114A5CA0905D0476DBDB7C50B1BB" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A</figureCitation>
); each appendage with subapical thorn-like process on the dorsomesal surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="988B930710717EEDCC4C2963D7C15296" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6A, C, D</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, with outer lateral margin expanded distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AC2A69A43D3F1E187BE838D5E8FAE47A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6D</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, spatulate, with truncate distal margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="40113E88D4B355BE660C6991802B7AA8" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6B</figureCitation>
). Phallic apparatus with phallotheca tubular, bearing basodorsal and basoventral pointed extensions; endotheca short, membranous, with 4 apical, robust, sclerotized spines; phallotremal sclerite simple, large, L-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EE2FE294D7B4DA41FFBC8956C26AB5F" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Chimarra (Otarrha) paraodonta sp. nov., holotype male genitalia: A left lateral view; B dorsal view; C ventral view; D left inferior appendage, dorsal view; E phallus, left lateral view; F phallus, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689956" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">6E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="F7ED398CB5A05FD6135D63D4254404FD" doi="10.3897/asp.80.e76559.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689955" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
